{"id":"project-LICHEN-w1a0","title":"loadng.c: Incorrect LRU comparison in seen table uses uninitialized reference","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/loadng.c
Lines: 415-425

In lichen_loadng_seen_check_and_mark(), the LRU slot selection has a bug:

    size_t slot = 0;
    uint32_t oldest_time = UINT32_MAX;
    for (size_t i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(seen_table); i++) {
        if (!seen_table[i].active) {
            slot = i;
            break;
        }
        if ((now_ms - seen_table[i].seen_at_ms) > (now_ms - oldest_time)) {
            oldest_time = seen_table[i].seen_at_ms;
            slot = i;
        }
    }

The comparison '(now_ms - oldest_time)' where oldest_time=UINT32_MAX causes unsigned wraparound. The comparison doesn't find the oldest entry correctly.

The correct approach should directly compare seen_at_ms values, or track elapsed time correctly. With the current logic, slot 0 will always be selected if no free slots exist, defeating the LRU eviction intent.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:49:29.029376Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:49:29.029409Z"}

